Bio Martín Abadi is Professor of Computer Science at UCSC (since 2001) and Principal Researcher at Microsoft (since 2006). Earlier, he studied at Stanford University and worked at Digital’s System Research Center and other industrial labs. His research is mainly on computer and network security, on programming languages, and on verification. He has contributed, for example, to the design and analysis of security protocols and to the foundations of object-oriented languages. In 2007, his research on security was recognized with the Outstanding Innovation Award of the ACM Special Interest Group on Security, Audit and Control (ACM SIGSAC), and with the Hall of Fame Award of the ACM Special Interest Group on Operating Systems.